# Cursor Rule: Flutter Code Best Practices

## Purpose
Ensure high-quality Flutter code that follows industry standards, maintains consistency, and passes all lint checks.

## 🚨 ABSOLUTE REQUIREMENTS - NO EXCEPTIONS 🚨

### MUST USE:
- ✅ `AppTypography` for **ALL** text styles - every single `Text` widget
- ✅ `LayoutConstants` for **ALL** spacing, padding, margins, dimensions

### MUST NOT USE:
- ❌ Hard-coded font sizes (e.g., `fontSize: 16`)
- ❌ Hard-coded spacing values (e.g., `padding: 8`, `SizedBox(height: 12)`)
- ❌ Hard-coded dimensions (e.g., `width: 44`, `size: 24`)
- ❌ `TextStyle()` with numeric font size
- ❌ Any numeric literal for UI sizing

**Violations of these rules will result in immediate code rejection.**

## Code Quality & Linting

### Always run flutter lint before committing
- Execute `flutter analyze` to check for lint issues
- Fix all lint violations before submitting code
- Use `flutter format` to auto-format code

### Lint Rules Compliance
Follow the `very_good_analysis` ruleset (version 6.0.0) with these exceptions:
- `public_member_api_docs: false` (API docs not required for private app)
- `avoid_dynamic_calls: false` (allowed for flexibility with external APIs)

### Common Lint Fixes
- **prefer_const_constructors**: Always use `const` for compile-time constants
- **prefer_final_fields**: Mark class fields `final` when not reassigned
- **avoid_print**: Use proper logging instead of print statements
- **prefer_single_quotes**: Use single quotes for strings
- **sort_child_properties_last**: Put child widgets last in widget constructors

## Architecture & Patterns

### BLoC Pattern
- Use BLoC for state management in complex screens
- Separate business logic from UI in Bloc classes
- Use `BlocBuilder`, `BlocListener`, and `BlocConsumer` appropriately
- Keep Bloc classes in `lib/screen/*/bloc/` directories

### Clean Architecture Layers
```
lib/
├── gateway/     # API clients & external data sources
├── service/     # Business logic & data processing
├── model/       # Data models & entities
├── screen/      # UI screens & routing
├── view/        # Reusable UI components
├── util/        # Utility functions & helpers
├── theme/       # Styling & design tokens
└── widgets/     # Custom widgets
```

### Dependency Injection
- Use `get_it` for dependency injection
- Register services in `lib/common/injector.dart`
- Access services via `injector<T>()` calls

## Widget Best Practices

### Widget Structure
- Prefer `StatelessWidget` when possible, use `StatefulWidget` only when necessary
- Use meaningful widget names (e.g., `PlaylistCarouselView`, `ArtworkItemView`)
- Keep widgets focused on single responsibilities
- Break complex widgets into smaller, reusable components

### Constructor Best Practices
```dart
class MyWidget extends StatelessWidget {
  const MyWidget({
    super.key,
    required this.title,
    this.subtitle,
    this.onTap,
  });

  final String title;
  final String? subtitle;
  final VoidCallback? onTap;

  // Good: const constructor with proper parameter naming
}
```

### State Management
- Use `ValueNotifier` for simple local state
- Use BLoC for complex state that needs to persist or be shared
- Avoid setState() for complex state management
- Use keys for widgets that need to maintain state across rebuilds

### Touch Targets & Accessibility
- **Minimum tappable area**: Ensure all interactive elements have at least 44x44 pixels
- **If parent size is smaller**: Adjust padding/gaps to meet the 44x44 minimum requirement
- **Accessibility compliance**: Follow WCAG guidelines for touch target sizes
- **Consistent touch feedback**: Provide visual feedback for all interactive elements

## Code Style & Conventions

### Naming Conventions
- **Classes**: PascalCase (e.g., `PlaylistService`, `ArtworkModel`)
- **Methods/Functions**: camelCase (e.g., `fetchPlaylists()`, `formatDate()`)
- **Variables**: camelCase (e.g., `playlistTitle`, `isLoading`)
- **Constants**: UPPER_SNAKE_CASE (e.g., `MAX_RETRY_COUNT`)
- **Private members**: Prefix with underscore (e.g., `_isLoading`)

### File Organization
- One class per file (except for closely related classes like models)
- Group related functionality in feature directories
- Use clear, descriptive file names
- Keep files under 500 lines when possible

### Imports
```dart
// Good: Group imports logically
import 'dart:async';
import 'dart:convert';

import 'package:flutter/material.dart';
import 'package:flutter_bloc/flutter_bloc.dart';

import 'package:autonomy_flutter/model/playlist.dart';
import 'package:autonomy_flutter/service/playlist_service.dart';
import 'package:autonomy_flutter/util/constants.dart';

// Local imports
import 'playlist_state.dart';
import 'playlist_event.dart';
```

## Error Handling

### Async Operations
- Always handle errors in async functions
- Use try-catch blocks for critical operations
- Log errors appropriately using the logging system
- Show user-friendly error messages

```dart
// Good: Proper error handling
Future<void> loadData() async {
  try {
    final data = await apiService.fetchData();
    emit(DataLoaded(data));
  } catch (e) {
    log.error('Failed to load data: $e');
    emit(DataError('Unable to load data. Please try again.'));
  }
}
```

### Null Safety
- Use null-safe operators (`?.`, `??`, `!`)
- Prefer nullable types when data might be absent
- Use `late` keyword only when initialization is guaranteed

## Performance Optimization

### Build Optimization
- Avoid unnecessary rebuilds by using `const` constructors
- Use `const` widgets in lists when possible
- Implement `shouldRebuild` in custom widgets when needed
- Use `ValueListenableBuilder` for reactive UI updates

### Memory Management
- Dispose controllers, streams, and listeners in `dispose()`
- Cancel subscriptions and timers
- Use weak references when appropriate
- Avoid memory leaks from closures capturing large objects

### Image Optimization
- Use appropriate image formats (WebP preferred)
- Implement proper caching with `cached_network_image`
- Use `cacheWidth` and `cacheHeight` for image optimization
- Lazy load images in lists

### Rendering Performance
- **Minimize saveLayer() calls**: Avoid `saveLayer()` when possible, use static shapes or refactor to avoid overlaps
- **Use opacity wisely**: Prefer `AnimatedOpacity` or `FadeInImage` over `Opacity` widget, especially in animations
- Apply opacity directly to images rather than wrapping in `Opacity` widget when possible
- Draw shapes with semitransparent colors instead of `Opacity` widget when possible
- **Use clipping carefully**: Clipping is expensive, use `borderRadius` instead of clipping for rounded rectangles
- Avoid `Clip.antiAliasWithSaveLayer` unless necessary

### Layout Optimization
- **Avoid intrinsic operations**: Don't use widgets that trigger intrinsic layout passes (like `IntrinsicHeight`, `IntrinsicWidth`)
- Set fixed sizes for grid/list cells when possible to avoid intrinsic calculations
- Use custom `RenderObject` for complex sizing requirements instead of intrinsic operations

### Animation Performance
- Avoid `Opacity` widget in animations; use `AnimatedOpacity` instead
- Don't put non-animated subtrees in `AnimatedBuilder.builder` function
- Avoid clipping in animations; pre-clip images when possible
- Use GPU fragment shaders for fading effects (`FadeInImage`)

### Frame Rate Target
- **Target 60fps**: Build and render frames in 16ms or less
- Enable "Show widget rebuild information" in IDE Flutter Performance window

## Testing

### Unit Tests
- Write tests for business logic in services
- Use `mocktail` for mocking dependencies
- Place tests in `test/unit-tests/`
- Follow existing test naming conventions

### Widget Tests
- Test complex widget behavior
- Use `flutter_test` for widget testing
- Mock external dependencies
- Test both success and error states

## Design System Integration

### ⚠️ CRITICAL RULE - READ THIS FIRST ⚠️

**ALL text styles MUST use `AppTypography`**  
**ALL spacing/sizing MUST use `LayoutConstants`**  
**NO hard-coded numbers allowed - ZERO EXCEPTIONS**

Any code with hard-coded font sizes, spacing, or dimensions will be **immediately rejected**.

### Typography and Layout Constants (MANDATORY)
**ALWAYS use `AppTypography` for text styles and `LayoutConstants` for sizing, padding, and spacing.**

⚠️ **ABSOLUTE REQUIREMENT - NO EXCEPTIONS:**
- ❌ **NEVER, EVER use hard-coded font sizes** (e.g., `fontSize: 16`)
- ❌ **NEVER, EVER use hard-coded spacing/padding values** (e.g., `padding: 16`, `height: 44`)
- ❌ **NEVER, EVER use TextStyle() directly** without AppTypography
- ❌ **NEVER, EVER use numeric literals** for spacing, dimensions, or sizes
- ✅ **ONLY use `AppTypography` methods for ALL text**
- ✅ **ONLY use `LayoutConstants` for ALL spacing, padding, and sizing**

**This is not optional. Code reviews will reject any hard-coded values.**

#### AppTypography - Text Styles
- Use `AppTypography` methods with BuildContext for all text
- Use extension methods for colors (`.black`, `.white`, `.grey`, etc.)
- **NO exceptions - even for one-off cases, use AppTypography**

```dart
// ✅ CORRECT: Using AppTypography
Text(
  'Playlist Title',
  style: AppTypography.h2(context).black,
)

Text(
  'Description text',
  style: AppTypography.body(context).grey,
)

// ❌ FORBIDDEN: Hard-coded styles - WILL BE REJECTED
Text(
  'Playlist Title',
  style: TextStyle(fontSize: 22, fontWeight: FontWeight.bold),
)

// ❌ FORBIDDEN: Direct font size - WILL BE REJECTED
Text(
  'Description',
  style: TextStyle(fontSize: 16, color: Colors.grey),
)

// ❌ FORBIDDEN: Any numeric font size - WILL BE REJECTED
Text(
  'Title',
  style: Theme.of(context).textTheme.bodyText1?.copyWith(fontSize: 18),
)
```

#### LayoutConstants - Spacing and Sizing
- Use `LayoutConstants` for **ALL** spacing values - **NO numeric literals allowed**
- Use the 4px grid system: `space1` (4px), `space2` (8px), `space3` (12px), `space4` (16px), etc.
- Use predefined constants for touch targets and icon sizes
- **If a spacing value isn't in LayoutConstants, add it - DON'T hard-code it**

```dart
// ✅ CORRECT: Using LayoutConstants
Padding(
  padding: EdgeInsets.all(LayoutConstants.space4),
  child: Column(
    children: [
      Icon(
        Icons.playlist,
        size: LayoutConstants.iconSizeLarge,
      ),
      SizedBox(height: LayoutConstants.space3),
      Text('Playlist', style: AppTypography.h3(context)),
    ],
  ),
)

// ✅ CORRECT: Touch target compliance
Container(
  height: LayoutConstants.minTouchTarget,
  width: LayoutConstants.minTouchTarget,
  child: IconButton(icon: Icon(Icons.more)),
)

// ❌ FORBIDDEN: Hard-coded spacing - WILL BE REJECTED
Padding(
  padding: EdgeInsets.all(16), // ❌ NO! Use LayoutConstants.space4
  child: Column(
    children: [
      Icon(Icons.playlist, size: 24), // ❌ NO! Use LayoutConstants.iconSizeLarge
      SizedBox(height: 12), // ❌ NO! Use LayoutConstants.space3
      Text('Playlist'), // ❌ NO! Use AppTypography
    ],
  ),
)

// ❌ FORBIDDEN: Hard-coded dimensions - WILL BE REJECTED
Container(
  height: 44, // ❌ NO! Use LayoutConstants.minTouchTarget
  width: 44,  // ❌ NO! Use LayoutConstants.minTouchTarget
  child: IconButton(icon: Icon(Icons.more)),
)

// ❌ FORBIDDEN: Any numeric literals for spacing - WILL BE REJECTED
Column(
  children: [
    SizedBox(height: 8),  // ❌ NO! Use LayoutConstants.space2
    Container(padding: EdgeInsets.symmetric(horizontal: 20)), // ❌ NO!
  ],
)
```

#### When to Use What
- **Headings**: Use `AppTypography.h1` through `AppTypography.h4` based on hierarchy
- **Body text**: Use `AppTypography.body` (default) or `AppTypography.bodySmall` (sparingly)
- **Metadata**: Use `AppTypography.caption` for low-priority information
- **Technical text**: Use `AppTypography.mono` for addresses, code
- **Small gaps**: `LayoutConstants.space1` or `space2` (4-8px)
- **Default spacing**: `LayoutConstants.space4` (16px)
- **Section spacing**: `LayoutConstants.space6` or `space8` (24-32px)
- **Icons**: Use `iconSizeSmall`, `iconSizeDefault`, `iconSizeMedium`, `iconSizeLarge`

#### 🚫 Absolutely Forbidden - Will Result in Code Rejection
```dart
// ❌ NEVER DO THIS - ANY OF THESE WILL BE REJECTED:
fontSize: 16
padding: EdgeInsets.all(20)
height: 44
SizedBox(width: 12)
Icon(Icons.x, size: 24)
TextStyle(fontSize: 14)
Container(margin: EdgeInsets.symmetric(vertical: 8))
```

**Remember: If you're typing a number for size/spacing/font, you're doing it wrong.**

### Design Tokens
- Use design tokens from `/lib/design/build/` for consistent styling
- Reference typography tokens for text styles via `AppTypography`
- Use spacing tokens via `LayoutConstants`
- Avoid hard-coded values when tokens are available

### Responsive Design
- Use `ResponsiveLayout` utilities for adaptive layouts
- Test layouts on different screen sizes
- Consider tablet layouts where appropriate
- Use `MediaQuery` for responsive spacing

## Code Commit Guidelines

### Never Auto-Commit Code
- **Do NOT automatically commit or stage code changes**
- Always provide the user with a conventional commit message after making changes
- Use the format: `type(scope): description`

### Conventional Commit Format
```
type(scope): brief description

[optional body explaining changes]

[optional footer with breaking changes]
```

**Types:**
- `feat`: New feature
- `fix`: Bug fix
- `docs`: Documentation changes
- `style`: Code style changes (formatting, etc.)
- `refactor`: Code refactoring
- `test`: Adding/modifying tests
- `chore`: Maintenance tasks

**Scopes (common for Flutter apps):**
- `ui`, `widget`, `view`: UI components
- `bloc`, `state`, `event`: State management
- `api`, `service`, `gateway`: Data layer
- `model`, `entity`: Data models
- `util`, `helper`: Utility functions
- `theme`, `style`: Styling/theming

**Examples:**
```
feat(playlist): add carousel view for artwork display

fix(auth): resolve login timeout issue

refactor(playlist-service): extract common playlist operations

style(artwork-widget): fix lint issues and formatting
```

